let's calculate the number of rides of each age range

In [49]:
def create_list_age_range() :
    i = 0
    age_range_dict = {"[0,20]":0,"[21,30]":0,"[31,40]":0,"[41,50]":0,"[51,60]":0,"[61,70]":0,"[71,80]":0,"[80,+]":0}

    for e in df_use["membre_age"] :
        if e <= 20  :
            age_range_dict["[0,20]"] = age_range_dict["[0,20]"] + 1
        elif( e > 20 and e <= 30):
            age_range_dict["[21,30]"] = age_range_dict["[21,30]"] + 1
        elif( e > 30 and e <= 40):
            age_range_dict["[31,40]"] = age_range_dict["[31,40]"] + 1
        elif( e > 40 and e <= 50):
            age_range_dict["[41,50]"] = age_range_dict["[41,50]"] + 1
        elif( e > 50 and e <= 60):
            age_range_dict["[51,60]"] = age_range_dict["[51,60]"] + 1
        elif( e > 60 and e <= 70):
            age_range_dict["[61,70]"] = age_range_dict["[61,70]"] + 1
        elif( e > 70 and e <= 80):
            age_range_dict["[71,80]"] = age_range_dict["[71,80]"] + 1
        else : 
            age_range_dict["[80,+]"] = age_range_dict["[80,+]"] + 1
    return age_range_dict

Conclusions¶

main conclusion¶

we can see that almost all users of this service have almost the same behaviours concerning duration time undependently on gender or age-range,they folow the same pattern

other facts¶

  • most users fall between 20-40 years old
  • most users of this service are males
  • most users of this service are subscribed
